properties.areaDesc: Southern Inner Channels; Cape Decision to Salisbury Sound Coastal Area; Dixon Entrance to Cape Decision Coastal Area; Inner Channels from Kupreanof Island to Etolin Island
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 1 at 5:22AM AKST until February 1 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Snow accumulations of 2 to 7 inches.

* WHERE...Portions of the Eastern Gulf Coast, the Southeast Gulf
Coast, the central Inner Channels, and the southern Inner
Channels including Ketchikan, Sitka, Petersburg, Wrangell,
Craig, Klawock, and Thorne Bay.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM AKST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Travel may be
difficult. Visibility will be very poor in snow squalls.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Amounts will be highly variable. There will
be periods of sun as well as snow squalls.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM AKST THIS EVENING
